+Phase 8 — Player-Facing UX Layer
 Goal
 
-Move from:
+Turn the current loop from:
 
-isolated NPC minds reacting to player/world events
+simulation → scene → narration → choices
 
-To:
-
-NPCs and factions influencing each other through:
-alliances
-betrayals
-rumor spread
-group decisions
+Into a richer player-facing experience with:
 
+dialogue mode
+interaction mode
+scene state / active speaker
+journal / codex surfacing
+encounter mode hooks
+visible world consequences
+player-facing history and quest signals
 Design rules
-
-deterministic only
-bounded lists/maps
-serialized state everywhere
-no random spread
-no direct narrator-owned state
-social outputs must become simulation events/consequences first
-New systems in Phase 6.5
